cs.GT, cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA 

Reasoning: 
- cs.GT (Game Theory): The paper explicitly mentions potential games and analyzes a game for power and frequency allocation. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper focuses on wireless networks and their power and frequency allocation. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper uses the physical SINR model to validate a successful allocation. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the goal of achieving some SINR requirement and evaluates the performance of the proposed game. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems): The paper analyzes a game where multiple access points are involved in power and frequency allocation.
